00046 /* The print handler is installed by calling the cbLOG_registerPrintHandler.
00047  * When the cbLOG_print function is called, the print handler is invoked.
00048  * Hence, the implementation of a print is user defined. The input to the
00049  * print handler is the same as for the ANSI C vprintf function.
00050  */
00051 typedef enum
00052 {
00053     cbLOG_LEVEL_0, // Logging is turned off
00054     cbLOG_LEVEL_1, // Only errors are logged
00055     cbLOG_LEVEL_2, // All functions/callbacks except data are logged
00056     cbLOG_LEVEL_3, // All functions/callbacks including data are logged
00057 } cbLOG_Level;
00058 
00059 typedef enum
00060 {
00061     cbLOG_COLOR_BLACK  = 0,
00062     cbLOG_COLOR_BLUE = 1,
00063     cbLOG_COLOR_GREEN = 2,
00064     cbLOG_COLOR_CYAN = 3,
00065     cbLOG_COLOR_RED = 4,
00066     cbLOG_COLOR_MAGENTA = 5,
00067     cbLOG_COLOR_BROWN = 6,
00068     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTGREY = 7,
00069     cbLOG_COLOR_DARKGREY = 8,
00070     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTBLUE = 9,
00071     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTGREEN = 10,
00072     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTCYAN = 11,
00073     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTRED = 12,
00074     cbLOG_COLOR_LIGHTMAGENTA = 13,
00075     cbLOG_COLOR_YELLOW = 14,
00076     cbLOG_COLOR_WHITE = 15
00077 } cbLOG_Color;
